def: An outer garment for men or women, originally of fur, or linedwith fur; a lady's outer garment, made of silk or other fabric.
The principal or ruling evil spirit. E. Arnold.
To carry away or mislead wrongfully, as by passion. [Obs.] Bp.Hall.

In an occasional manner; on occasion; at times, as conveniencerequires or opportunity offers; not regularly. Stewart.The one, Wolsey, directly his subject by birth; the other, hissubject occasionally by his preferment. Fuller.
Lulled to sleep. [Obs.] Dr. H. More.
Having four horns, or hornlike organs; as, a quadricornousbeetle.
The art or process of coloring metals.
A kind of buttress of masonry to strengthen a revetment wall.
